						<summary>

						<p>Slab setup in front of the Basavēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1034 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that <hi rend="italic">danḍanāyaka</hi> Chākimayya made a grant of 6 <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> of land to the god Mahādēva of Biyāḷkaṟike.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 956 Bhāva, Śrā[vaṇa]. It may correspond with 1034 A.D., July 19 to August 16.</p>						

						</summary>
